title: President Biden Announces Presidential Delegation to the Republic of Cabo Verde to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency José Maria Neves | The White House
content: President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. today announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Republic of Cabo Verde to attend the Inauguration of His Excellency José Maria Neves on November 9, 2021, in Praia, Cabo Verde.The Honorable Martin J. Walsh, Secretary of Labor of the United States, will lead the delegation.Members of the Presidential Delegation:The Honorable Martin J. Walsh, Secretary of Labor of the United StatesThe Honorable Jeff Daigle, United States Ambassador to Cabo VerdeThe Honorable Hakeem Jeffries, United States Member of Congress (D), New York and Chair of the House Democratic CaucusThe Honorable Dana Banks, Special Assistant to the President and National Security Council Senior Director for Africa###
